{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DataTransferItemList.add()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItemList/add","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTML_Drag_and_Drop_API\">HTML Drag and Drop API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItemList\"><code>DataTransferItemList</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItemList/length\"><code>length</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><em><code>add()</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItemList/clear\"><code>clear()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItemList/remove\"><code>remove()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for HTML Drag and Drop API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransfer\"><code>DataTransfer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItem\"><code>DataTransferItem</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DragEvent\"><code>DragEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>DataTransferItemList.add()</code></strong> method creates a new\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItem\"><code>DataTransferItem</code></a> using the specified data and adds it to the drag data\n  list. The item may be a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a> or a string of a\n  given type. If the item is successfully added to the list, the newly-created\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItem\"><code>DataTransferItem</code></a> object is returned.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">add(data, type)\nadd(file)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"data\"><code>data</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A string representing the drag item's data.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><code>type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      A string of the drag item's type. Some example types are\n      <code>text/html</code> and <code>text/plain</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"file\"><code>file</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a> object. No type needs to be given in this case.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItem\"><code>DataTransferItem</code></a> containing the specified data. If the drag item\n  couldn't be created (for example, if the associated <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransfer\"><code>DataTransfer</code></a> object\n  has no data store), <code>null</code> is returned.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"notsupportederror\"><code>NotSupportedError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Thrown if the string <code>data</code> parameter was provided, and the list already contains an\n      item whose <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DataTransferItem/kind\" title=\"kind\"><code>kind</code></a> is <code>\"Plain Unicode string\"</code> and\n      whose type is equal to the specified type parameter.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This example shows the use of the <code>add()</code> method.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"html","title":"HTML","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=